column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
4 inches low.  Drought conditions most of the summer.
4 inches low.  Partly cloudy wind from the NW.
2 inches low.  10 days ago algae present in lake and halfway through the narrows.  Mccullough Lake was clear.
Sunny- wind 5 mph.  Algae in water.
Sunny- no wind.  Water temp. 64 F.  Lake depth 16'.  Water normal.  Spring rains.
Water temp 72 F.  Pollen from pine trees.  Sunny.
Water temp 68 F.  Lake in bloom.  Air temp. 72 F.  Sunny- no wind.
Water temp. 77 F.  Air 76 F.  Bloom strongest in 4 years.  Heavy weed growth.  Satellite path 24.
Satellite 24.  Partly cloudy- water temp. 72 F.  Air temp. 74 F.  Lake in heavy bloom.
Air temp 62 F.  Water temp 66 F.  Lake bloom dissipating.  Lake down a little.  Satellite path 25.
Air temp. 74 F.  Water 64 F.  Less lake bloom.  Windy.
Air 55 F- water 62 F.  Very clear- very calm.
Light overcast- air 72 F- water 60 F.  Water level normal.
Air temp 66 F- water temp 64 F- creek running after rain- particles suspended in water.
Air 84 F- water 77 F.  Very clear water.  A little algae.  Rain this week.
Air 84 F- water 74 F.  Water 3" high.  Very clear - slight wind.
Air 80 F- water 75 F.  Water level normal- down 3"- no wind.
Air 90 F- humid.  Water 82 F.  Light wind.  Water very clear.  Partly cloudy.
Air 84 F- water 82 F.  Very clear - good weed growth.  Water down 2-3".
Air 84 F- water 72 F.  Had heavy rain 7/23.  No major runoff into lake.
Sunny- air 68 F.  Water level down about 4" from ice out.  Lake depth 16'.
71 F air temp.  Visiblity 7 ft.  Sunny- calm.  Water level normal.  65 F water.
Sunny- light breeze.  Water is down 6".  Water is the clearest we have seen.
Slightly cloudy.  Water very clear.  No bloom all summer.  Air temp 64 F.
Sunny- calm.  Air 74 F.  Water is getting warmer.
Air temp 72F- surface 69.8. Water color more normal after spring runoff
Air temp 82.3F. Water color much clearer after all the rain last month.
